# Development Workflow (Obsidian → Cursor → Unity → Git)

Canonical process: `docs/PrisonEscape/06 Process/Development Workflow.md`. **No exceptions.**

## The loop

```
Brainstorm → Obsidian spec → Implement → Agent verify → YOU playtest → Sync vault → Devlog → Git (only when YOU say so)
```

| Phase | Who | When |
|-------|-----|------|
| Design | Agent + you | Before code — vault spec exists or you approve creating one |
| Implement | Agent | After spec; **one small slice** per `feat/...` branch off `dev` (prefer a worktree — `git-worktrees.mdc`). Policy: `docs/PrisonEscape/06 Process/Small PRs & Feature Slices.md` |
| Agent verify | Agent | After code — compile, Unity MCP, EditMode tests, layout rebuild logs |
| **Playtest** | **You** | **Before commit/push** for anything affecting gameplay, UI, layout, or scenes |
| Sync + devlog | Agent | Before asking you to commit — vault and devlog must match reality |
| Git record | Agent | **Only when you explicitly say commit and/or push in that message** |

## HARD GATE — commit & push (agent MUST enforce)

**Never run `git commit`, `git push`, `gh pr create`, or `gh pr merge` unless ALL are true:**

1. You **explicitly requested** commit/push/PR in the **same message** (not implied by "keep going" or "looks good").
2. The end-of-task checklist below was presented with ✅/❌/⚠️.
3. **Playtest gate passed** (see next section) — or you gave an **explicit written waiver** in chat: e.g. `skip playtest, commit anyway`.

If you ask to commit without playtest confirmation → **STOP. Do not commit.** Present the playtest gate and ask again.

If you ask to skip checklist items → **STOP.** List what's missing and ask how to proceed.

## HARD GATE — playtest (before any commit/push)

For changes touching **code, scenes, UI, layout, or gameplay**:

1. Agent completes technical verify (compile, MCP, tests).
2. Agent gives you a **short playtest script** (what to open, what to click, what to look for).
3. Agent asks: **"Have you playtested this in Unity? (pass / fail / not yet)"**
4. **Do not commit until:**
   - You reply **pass** (or describe fixes → agent fixes → you re-test), OR
   - You reply **skip playtest, commit anyway** with a one-line reason.

Doc-only or rule-only changes with zero runtime impact: playtest gate may be marked N/A — state that explicitly in the checklist.

## End-of-task checklist (present before "done" or commit)

| Step | Required before commit? |
|------|-------------------------|
| Spec — vault notes updated | Yes (unless doc-only typo) |
| Status — Systems Overview / feature spec current | Yes |
| Devlog — entry in `Prison Escape Devlog Dashboard.md` | Yes |
| Code — matches vault; `.meta` with new assets | Yes |
| Agent verify — compile / MCP / tests | Yes for code changes |
| **Your playtest** — pass, fail, N/A, or waived | **Yes — gate** |
| Graph — `graphify-out/` refreshed or noted stale | Yes for code changes |
| Git — correct branch; **your explicit commit/push request** | **Yes — gate** |

**Do not say "done", "all set", or "ready to merge" until you confirm the checklist.**

## What the agent does when you forget

- Remind you of the gate instead of committing silently.
- Refuse commit/push until playtest is confirmed or explicitly waived.
- If you used a diff-tab or UI "commit" action: run the checklist first, report gaps, ask before executing git.
- Opening/updating a PR requires the same gates as commit/push.

## Ask first — always

- Commit, push, PR, merge to `main`
- Skipping playtest, devlog, or vault sync
- Design changes without a vault update
- Excluding files you may expect tracked (screenshots, `.meta`, vault notes)
- Opening a **mega-PR** that mixes unrelated systems (requires explicit waiver). Prefer slices per `docs/PrisonEscape/06 Process/Small PRs & Feature Slices.md`.

## Where updates go

| Change | Location |
|--------|----------|
| Game design / UI / layout | `docs/PrisonEscape/` |
| Technical / test docs | `05 Engineering/` or `Assets/Docs/` |
| Milestones | `Prison Escape Devlog Dashboard.md` |
| UI surfaces | `03 Systems/UI & HUD.md` + matching note under `03 Systems/UI/` |
